<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editor of Blythe's twice-weekly newspaper said the state attorney general 
has told him that refusal by the town's only movie theater to admit the paper's 
part-time movie critic may violate California's civil rights law. But, said 
Harold Stanford, editor of the Palo Verde Valley Times, Atty. Gen. John K. Van 
de Kamp has advised him to seek an amicable settlement. Stanford, who has been 
sending critic Cathy Monnett more than 60 miles to Yuma to review films, said 
Van de Kamp has not responded to his request that the state file suit against 
the theater. Monnett was banned from the theater Dec. 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
