<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A proposal to allow gay and lesbian couples to live in married-student housing 
is being considered by UC Berkeley lawyers and administrators before being 
submitted to Chancellor Ira Michael Heyman, according to a campus housing 
official. Proponents of the proposal claim that UC policy against 
discrimination based on sexual orientation makes the rule allowing only legally 
married couples in that housing unfair to homosexual couples. 
</P>
