<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 DETECTIVES ALMOST HIT BY CAR; DRIVER ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Sun Valley man was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder and grand theft 
Tuesday night after he tried to run over detectives who were gathering 
information for a search warrant, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Two Glendale detectives went to the home of Stephen Urquidez in the 7700 block 
of Shadycove Avenue about 5:15 p.m. Tuesday to "scan out the area" for 
information to obtain a search warrant, Police Sgt. Mike Rock said. He said 
Urquidez, 26, is suspected of stealing an automobile in Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
The detectives, who were in street clothes, were approaching the house when 
Urquidez, who had just driven up, backed into the street and tried to run over 
them, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The detectives fired at Urquidez, who drove away, police said. He was 
apprehended about an hour later in the 2300 block of Cove Way in Silver Lake, 
Rock said. 
</P>
<P>
Urquidez was being held without bail in the Glendale Jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
