MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Flu has hit the Los Angeles Philharmonic. Orchestra Manager Nancybell Coe 
reports that 10 of the orchestra's 75 instrumentalists scheduled to play a 
Beethoven/Schubert program last week were out with the flu bug. The sick group 
included Principal Concertmaster Sidney Weiss. "Because the program did not 
require a full orchestra, and because only one player was taking the week off 
anyway, we had to hire only two substitutes," says Coe. What will happen when 
the Philharmonic meets today for its first rehearsal of this week, no one is 
predicting. . . . ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
