<P>
STANFORD FRESHMAN APPLICATIONS DROP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STANFORD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman applications to Stanford declined for the second year in a row, 
according to the school's Undergraduate Admissions Office. 
</P>
<P>
The office reported on Tuesday that frosh applications dropped about 6% this 
year to about 14,869. The school reported a similar decline in applicants a 
year ago. 
</P>
<P>
The office also said that among Stanford freshmen, the proportion applying to 
at least six other colleges doubled in the last five years, from 18% to 40%. 
</P>
<P>
Stanford admits students without regard to financial need, the office said. 
</P>
