<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
L. A. BAPTIST PAIR ANCHOR VICTORY OVER VILLAGE CHRISTIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROCKY PINHEIRO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What started out as the J. D. Strong show segued into the Reid Chobanian hour 
as L. A. Baptist took a 61-52 Alpha League victory over Village Christian at L. 
A. Baptist and pulled to within 1 game of the first-place Crusaders. 
</P>
<P>
Strong got the Knights off to a fast start with 2 steals, 2 rebounds and 8 of 
his team's 15 points in the first quarter. But ultimately, it was Chobanian who 
was the difference for L. A. Baptist. The forward scored 11 of his game-high 17 
points in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
"I wanted this game for myself and the team," Chobanian said. "I felt I was in 
the right place at the right time." 
</P>
<P>
L. A. Baptist (16-6, 4-3 in league play) took a 32-28 halftime lead, but 
forward Mike Curl turned the momentum, scoring 9 points in the third quarter to 
pull Village Christian into a 41-41 tie by the end of the period. 
</P>
<P>
Village Christian (8-10, 5-2) came out in the fourth quarter to take a 
four-point lead behind the shooting of Scott Danielson, who fouled out with 45 
seconds to play, and David Brownfield. 
</P>
<P>
Curl fouled out with 3 minutes to play, leaving Village Christian with little 
offense. L. A. Baptist proceeded to build a margin that Village Christian could 
not bridge behind the shooting of Dave Unter -- who finished with 13 points -- 
and Chobanian. ROCKY PINHEIRO 
</P>
</TEXT>
