<TEXT>
<P>
In other boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 82, Hart 68 -- Senior point guard Edmundo Zepeda scored 25 points and 
added 10 assists and 7 rebounds as Burbank upset Hart in a Foothill League game 
at Hart. Adam Tunison added 20 points for Burbank (3-15, 2-5). Brett Wilson 
scored 25 points to lead Hart (11-10, 4-3). 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 74, Quartz Hill 73 -- Canyon trailed, 67-51, with 3:35 left but 
outscored Quartz Hill, 23-6, and won the Golden League game on Darren 
Oldenberg's 3-point basket with 2 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Oldenberg's shot gave Canyon (8-11, 3-4) its first lead of the game. Quartz 
Hill, which led, 73-64, with 1:30 remaining, missed 4 1-and-1 free-throw 
situations in the final minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Jermaine Nixon scored a team-high 23 points for Canyon and teammate Jamil 
Austin had 22. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs 62, Alhambra 47 -- Senior forward Dan Murphy scored a game-high 23 
points to lead the Indians in the Foothill League game. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy topped the 20-point mark for the 17th time this season. Burroughs (15-5, 
7-0) leads the league by 2 games with 3 to play. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 97, La Salle 52 -- The Knights rolled to their ninth consecutive win 
and remained undefeated in San Fernando Valley League play. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame (13-8, 7-0) has not lost since dropping a nonleague game to Pasadena 
on Dec. 28. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame was led by Brian Jones, who scored 26 of his game-high 30 points in 
the first half. Ken Hicks added 19 points and 10 assists, 8 in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff 71, St. Genevieve 47 -- Bell-Jeff knocked the Valiants 2 games out of 
first in the San Fernando Valley League with a win at Bell-Jeff. Nick 
Sanderson, who scored just 3 points in the first quarter, finished with 22 
points and 10 rebounds to lead Bell-Jeff (18-2, 6-1). St. Genevieve is 11-8, 
4-3 in league play. 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 77, Crescenta Valley 67 -- Pasadena's Don Mitchell was 11 of 12 from 
the field and scored 22 points to help the Bulldogs clinch the Pacific League 
title at Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 50, Arcadia 49 -- Robert DeTolve made 2 free throws with 8 seconds 
left to vault Glendale to the Pacific League victory. DeTolve scored 15 points 
and grabbed 8 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 53, Chaminade 49 -- Junior point guard Rick Osterloh hit a 12-foot jump 
shot with 4 minutes remaining to give Harvard the lead for good in the San 
Fernando Valley league game at Harvard. 
</P>
<P>
MEN 
</P>
<P>
Cal Baptist 79, Cal Lutheran 76 -- Steve deLaveaga scored a game-high 30 points 
and teammate Mike Demeter added 22, but no other Cal Lutheran player reached 
double figures in the Golden State Athletic Conference game at Cal Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
Redlands 74, Occidental 58 -- Occidental forward Kelly Stephenson scored a 
game-high 23 points, but Occidental was outscored, 38-23, in the first half of 
the Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Assn. game at Occidental. 
</P>
