<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS ELLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sockers midfielder Brian Quinn, a Major Indoor Soccer League All-Star the past 
3 seasons, is expected to be out for 3 weeks because of a strained left arch. 
</P>
<P>
Quinn, who has scored 20 points this season, hurt his arch during the Sockers' 
4-3 overtime loss in Dallas Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
It was originally thought that Quinn had torn a muscle in his foot and might 
miss up to 6 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Ron Newman also said that it is unlikely the Sockers will sign former 
Cleveland Force defender John Stollmeyer to replace recently retired Gary 
Etherington. 
</P>
<P>
Stollmeyer is a member of the United States national team, and Newman said he 
would miss nearly half of the Sockers' remaining games if he were signed. CHRIS 
ELLO 
</P>
