<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A firm owned by former heavyweight boxing champion Muhammad Ali filed suit in 
federal court in Los Angeles, seeking more than $550 million from two companies 
that allegedly signed contracts for big batches of Muhammad Ali shoe polish but 
then refused to accept them. The suit, filed in U.S. District Court, names the 
K mart Corp. and Melville Corp. and alleges racial discrimination, breach of 
contract, emotional distress, conspiracy and antitrust violations. Spokesmen 
for the two companies declined comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
