<P>
STARSIGNAL INTRODUCES COLOR FAX MACHINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAMPBELL, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
StarSignal Inc. has introduced what it said is the first facsimile machine 
capable of sending full-color pictures over conventional telephone lines. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the device, with a $19,000 price tag, will be aimed at the 
growing desktop publishing market and other uses that require fast transmission 
of color images. Existing facsimile machines are used primarily for 
communication. 
</P>
