<P>
SAUDIS EXTEND PILGRIMAGE QUOTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RIYADH, Saudi Arabia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saudi Arabia today announced that a quota system limiting pilgrims will remain 
in force during this year's Muslim pilgrimage to Islam's holiest shrines in 
Mecca and Medina. 
</P>
<P>
After deadly riots during the 1987 pilgrimage, which the Saudis blamed on Iran, 
the Saudi government declared that only one person out of every 1,000 people in 
Muslim countries would be allowed to visit the shrines. Previously, there were 
no restrictions. 
</P>
