<P>
GIRL KILLED, 3 INJURED IN CAR-TRUCK COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 13-year-old girl was killed Tuesday afternoon after the car in which she was 
riding turned left in front of a pickup truck and was struck broadside, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Another passenger in the car, a 19-year-old Anaheim man, was in very critical 
condition at UCI Medical Center in Orange, Anaheim Police Lt. Vince Howard 
said. The names of both the girl and the man were being withheld until their 
families could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the Camaro, Hermilo Sanchez, 18 of Anaheim, and the driver of the 
