<HEADLINE>
<P>
EIP MICROWAVE POSTS LOSS FOR QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EIP Microwave, Newport Beach, reported a loss of $192,000 for its first quarter 
ended Dec. 31, 1988, contrasted with a year-earlier loss of $729,000. Sales 
rose 26% to $3.1 million from $2.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
The current year's first-quarter loss included a pretax charge against 
operations of $1.1 million resulting from the write-down of certain assets 
associated with the company's realignment of technical, financial and 
management resources. Partially offsetting the loss was a gain of $748,000 
resulting from an accounting change. 
</P>
<P>
The company manufactures microwave test and measurement instruments used in the 
defense and telecommunications industries. 
</P>
