<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
WORTHY, 6 OTHERS JOIN ALL-STAR TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James Worthy of the Los Angeles Lakers was among seven players added today to 
the NBA Western Conference team for the Feb. 12 All-Star Game. 
</P>
<P>
The other reserves, chosen by the conference coaches, were guard Clyde Drexler 
and center Kevin Duckworth of Portland, guard John Stockton and center Mark 
Eaton of Utah, and forwards Tom Chambers of Phoenix and Chris Mullin of Golden 
State. 
</P>
<P>
Previously selected as starters in fan balloting were guards Magic Johnson of 
the Lakers and Dale Ellis of Seattle, center Akeem Olajuwon of Houston and 
forwards Karl Malone of Utah and Alex English of Denver. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Riley of the Lakers will coach the West team that will face the Eastern 
Conference team in the All-Star Game at Houston. 
</P>
</TEXT>
